text.0:
:police_car_light: HOAX: A Facebook account using the name and images of the governor of Kenya's Makueni County is fake.

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: Governor Kivutha Kibwana's official Facebook account is a page, not a personal profile: https://t.co/DXKxvll1wo
text.1:
A screenshot of a tweet from Muhoozi Kainerugaba, the senior presidential adviser for special operations in Uganda, with a warning to presidential candidate Robert Kyagulanyi is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: Lieutenant General Kainerugaba has dismissed the tweet as fake: https://t.co/IJb0xehYw5
text.2:
A tweeted image of a burnt double cabin pickup alongside a claim that it was set on fire by supporters of Bobi Wine, an opposition leader in Uganda, is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:camera_with_flash: The photo is from 2018 and the vehicle was damaged in an unrelated incident: https://t.co/9W26ECYY5u
text.3:
A video that has been viewed thousands of times on Twitter claiming to show recent violence in Zanzibar following the October election is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: The video is of the unrest that followed the disputed 2005 elections in Zanzibar: https://t.co/eIm8LlnuYc
text.4:
:police_car_light: HOAX: A link to a Google form guiding people on how to apply for soft loans offered by a firm called Mwananchi Loans is fake.

:money_with_wings: Mwananchi Loans is not a registered lender in Kenya: https://t.co/wjGwL7EQBA
text.5:
A Facebook post with a screenshot of a message from President Donald Trump endorsing Bobi Wine for Uganda’s presidency is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: The message is not on President Trump’s official Facebook page: https://t.co/E36d1hulzY
